snippet.title: Stephen King's THE STAND | Episode 2: "Pocket Savior" Review | SPOILERS
snippet.description:
My spoiler-filled review of 'The Stand' S01E02, "Pocket Savior" from director Tucker Gates and CBS All Access. The episode stars Jovan Adepo, Heather Graham, Nat Wolff, Amber Heard, Odessa Young, James Marsden, Owen Teague, and Alexander Skarsgard.

Premise: Musician Larry Underwood is on the cusp of his big break when "Captain Trips" strikes New York. Alone and wandering an empty city, he meets an alluring new acquaintance also desperate to escape. Meanwhile, an incarcerated Lloyd Henreid comes face-to-face with Randall Flagg, The Dark Man himself, who makes him an enticing offer. - from IMDb.

Thanks very much for watching! If you enjoyed this video, please hit that thumbs up, and share if you really enjoyed it. Most importantly, what did you think of 'The Stand' Episode 2?
